						<summary>

						<p>This record is damaged and dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 147[5], Pramādīcha, Śrāvaṇa, ba. 10, Śu[kravāra]</hi> corresponding probably to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1553 August 4, Friday,</hi> in the reign of <hi rend="bold">Sadāsivadēva-Mahārāya.</hi> It records a gift for burning lamps before the god Mallikārjunadēva <hi rend="bold">of Kaggallu,</hi> surnamed <hi rend="bold">Timmasamudra,</hi> in <hi rend="bold">Kōkāpura-sthaḷa</hi> situated in <hi rend="bold">Penugoṇḍe-rājya,</hi> a division of <hi rend="bold">Ṟodda-nāḍu.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
